content.description: An interesting ramp system on the right side of "Smedley's Playhouse" (2nd ramp system). Makes for the best approach to the Lizard Slabs. It received a couple new bolts and a scrub back in 2010 but is probably in need of some TLC.
content.location: 2nd ramp system encountered and the cleaner/drier of the 2. Just left of the big roofs.

content.description: An easier variation of Medicine Wheel side swiping the crux roof.
content.location: From the top of Excavator go left then re connect with the crack.

content.description: This is an awesome climb when clean and deserving of attention. Brutish in places. The bolted technical crux roof is at the beginning of this pitch but there is more sustained and physical climbing the entire way up. The variation out left is 10+
content.protection: Gear to 4" and 4 bolts. Some might use a 5" piece
content.location: Climb Excavator to an anchor. Medicine Wheel is the continuing roof and crack system above.

content.description: A nice climb (when clean) on the left side of the Lizard Slabs. Good protection and rests. Trend left from the belay above the top of "Ode To Do Dah Day". or scramble to the top of the crag and drop in (not recommended).
content.location: Left side of Lizard Slabs. Above "Ode To Do Dah Day"

content.description: Just right of Lichen It. A fun and varied route in the middle of the Lizard Slabs best approached via "Ode To Do Dah Day"
content.protection: 8 bolts, fixed pin and couple of tcu's
content.location: Smedley's Playhouse. Right of Lichen It and above Ode To Do Dah Day

content.description: The Crack that leads up to Medicine Wheel. Mostly good gear with 1 spot of spice
content.location: left side of the crag "Southwestern Wall"

pathTokens: Hwy 20 and North Cascades National Park
Walker Valley and Lake Cavanaugh Rd Crags
